[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi all, I'm trying to obtain the least element of a set of natural numbers. I did search through a couple of books for \"least element\" regarding sets but could not find any examples. I also searched zulip and found some clues, such as <code>Nat.find</code>, but I'm not sure how to use that to get a least element.</p>\n<p>I do have a hypothesis stating that the set S is nonempty, so it seems to me this should doable without much fanfare. Could someone please help? </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ht</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≠</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∅</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IsLeast</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 484557669,
        "sender_full_name": "Derek Rhodes",
        "timestamp": 1732640213
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can use <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=sInf#doc\">docs#sInf</a></p>",
        "id": 484558149,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1732640366
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hmm, that page is 404'ing for some reason</p>",
        "id": 484558306,
